        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 11:58AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1157 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles northeast of Krebs to 2 miles southeast
of Stuart. These storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arpelar...                        Hartshorne...
Haileyville...                    Mcalester...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Krebs...
Alderson...                       Haywood...
Dow...                            Bache...
Ashland...                        Savanna...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
